  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Sometimes, you may need to remove a ticket to fix an error, undo an accidental entry, or keep your records accurate without affecting sales and inventory data. Depending on the situation, you can either delete or void a ticket.</p><h4 id=\"DeleteorVoidaTicket-DeletingTickets\">Deleting Tickets</h4><p>Tickets can only be deleted if they are not in Closed status and do not contain any transaction information. If the ticket is eligible for deletion, remove all items, save the ticket, and delete it from the Ticket List.</p><h4 id=\"DeleteorVoidaTicket-VoidingTickets\">Voiding Tickets</h4><p>Voiding a closed ticket is often more efficient than processing a return because it automatically reverses payments and restocks any returned items. However, tickets can only be voided on the same business day they are closed. After that, tickets are locked and can no longer be voided. Tickets in Void status do not affect profitability reporting but remain in the system for historical records.</p><p>If you plan to void a ticket that has not been closed, we recommend removing all items, refunding any transactions, and closing the ticket. Once closed, you\u2019ll have until the end of the business day to void it.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: To void a ticket, you must have an assigned Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) with the correct payment methods configured.</p><h3 id=\"DeleteorVoidaTicket-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933541674/Searching+for+Tickets\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933541674\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Searching for Tickets</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933607055/Getting+Started+The+Ticket+Queue\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933607055\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Getting Started: The Ticket Queue</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1930494512/Creating+a+Quick+Sale+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1930494512\" data-linked-resource-version=\"14\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Creating a Quick Sale Ticket</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933279378/Virtual+Cash+Terminal+VCT+Refund+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933279378\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Issuing a Refund: Resources</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"DeleteorVoidaTicket-DeleteaTicket\">Delete a Ticket</h2><p>If a ticket has no items or transactions, you can delete it from your Ticket List. First, locate the ticket, click the <strong>Options</strong> button under the <strong>Actions</strong> column, and select <strong>Delete</strong> from the available actions. You will be asked to confirm deletion, and once deleted, you will receive confirmation that the ticket is completely removed from the system, with no records retained.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Void 6.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%206.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Void 7.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%207.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Void 8.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%208.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h2 id=\"DeleteorVoidaTicket-VoidaClosedTicket\">Void a Closed Ticket</h2><p>To void a ticket, you must have an assigned Virtual Cash Terminal (VCT) with the correct payment methods configured.</p><p>First locate the ticket you need to void. If needed, use the filters on the Ticket List to find tickets in <strong>Closed</strong> status. On the <strong>Ticket View</strong> page, click the <strong>Void</strong> button in the ticket actions row.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Void 1.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"442\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Clicking <strong>Void</strong> will reopen the ticket for review. The <strong>Void Ticket Items</strong> section will display any items that will be refunded and returned to inventory (if applicable). The <strong>Transactions</strong> section will generate a pending payout based on the original payment method.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>To complete the process, click <strong>Void</strong> at the bottom-right of the screen. You will be redirected to the <strong>Ticket View</strong> page, where you can print a receipt, add notes, and confirm that the ticket is now in <strong>Void</strong> status.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933541574/Void%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
